{"lemma":"طُنَّيْ","slug":"طُنَّيْ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27146","n27151","n27202","n27205","n27206"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hum, to buzz, to drone"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ring, to clang"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to move with buzzing sound, to whiz"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tonne, metric ton"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the human body","tags":["collective","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"load carried on the camel's back between the loads on both sides","tags":["collective","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bundle of reeds used as a bearing","tags":["collective","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Onomatopoeic.\n\nFrom English ton and French tonne (“ton”), from Latin tunna.\n\nThe meaning of a bundle of reed is considered from Aramaic טוּנַּס (ṭunnas, “reed”), which is attested once in Jewish Literary Aramaic and agrees with Ancient Greek δόναξ (dónax, “reed”), otherwise compare אֲטוּנָא (ʔăṭūnā), אֲטְוָנָא (ʔăṭwānā, “twisted strap”), which occurs in Jewish Babylonian Aramaic sometimes without the aleph prothesis.\nThe meaning of a load, as which also the human body is easily understood, is from the common Aramaic טוּנָא (ṭūna, ṭunnā), an assimilated form of טְוּעֲנָא (ṭūʕănā), טְעוּנָא (ṭəʕūnā, “load, burden”), which or a similar form is also the source of طَاعُون (ṭāʕūn, “plague”)."},"ipa":["/tˤann/","/tˤunn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27146","headword_ar":"طُنِّىٌّ","root":"Tn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large-bodied"},{"kind":"text","text":"man. (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27151","headword_ar":"طَنِيَ","root":"TnA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had his spleen adhering to his side."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And, said of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had a tertian fever, and his spleen in consequence became enlarged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.) Thus pronounced by some with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaniYa","text_ar":"طَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27202","headword_ar":"طَنِىَ","root":"TnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TanFY","text_ar":"طَنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) said of a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had his spleen adhering to his side in consequence of vehement thirst:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or, said of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had his spleen and his lungs adhering to the ribs on the left side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that, sometimes, they become putrid and black;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but mostly this is the case in camels; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATnY","text_ar":"اطنى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had a tertian fever, and his spleen in consequence became enlarged:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, * TA:) and, said of a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his spleen became enlarged in consequence of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disease of the lungs called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuHaAz","text_ar":"نُحَاز"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh, TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taniy^a","text_ar":"طَنِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. thereof.] ―         -b2-  And, said of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaniYa","text_ar":"ضَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, slender, and small in body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diseased, disordered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n27205","headword_ar":"طِنْىٌ","root":"TnY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bier:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tino'N","text_ar":"طِنْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumiYa fulaAnN","text_ar":"رُمِىَ فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Tinoyihi","text_ar":"فِى طِنْيِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY Tinoy^ihi","text_ar":"فى طِنْيِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY nayoTihi","text_ar":"فى نَيْطِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was cast into his bier;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, when he died. (TA.)       -A2-  See also the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27206","headword_ar":"طَنًى","root":"TnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adhering of the spleen to the side in consequence of vehement thirst."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaniYa","text_ar":"طَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is the inf. n.] ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Disease"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in a general sense]. (K, TA.) [Accord. to the CK, in this sense, and in other senses mentioned in this paragraph,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TanoYN","text_ar":"طَنْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is wrong.] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ashes in a state of extinction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tino'N","text_ar":"طِنْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TnA^","text_ar":"طنا"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Doubt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suspicion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil opinion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that occasions doubt"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; (K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TinoYN","text_ar":"طِنْىٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tino'N","text_ar":"طِنْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any kind. (TA.)       -A3-  See also 4, last sentence.       -A4-  And see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]}}